cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.GT, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a modification of the AlphaGo Zero/Leela Zero paradigm for playing Go using reinforcement learning. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also uses computer vision techniques to process the Go board, which suggests the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) category. Additionally, the paper discusses game theory concepts such as winrate and score difference, indicating the Game Theory (cs.GT) category. Finally, the paper uses reinforcement learning to train the agents, which falls under the category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
